metadata.name: Benjamin Danklin
metadata.description:
Benjamin Franklin was a large advocate for hemp. He explained that it was a more sustainable and renewable resource than other crops, and once famously declared “Hemp is not only profitable but necessary.” 

This is my reimagining of a world where Benjamin was an advocate for hemp for its recreational properties. So much so, that in this world, it’s earned him the moniker “Benjamin Danklin”.
